data.label: Account
data.description: Represents an individual account, which is an organization or person involved with your business (such as customers, competitors, and partners).

data.label: ActivityMetric
data.description: Represents activities that were added to Salesforce automatically by Einstein Activity Capture and manually by users.

data.label: ContractGroupPlan
data.description: Represents a set of plans as part of the contract between the insurance carrier and the group. This set of plans corresponds to the plans included in the quote (as Quote Line Items). Child object of Contract. This object is available in API version 55.0 and later.

data.label: InsurancePolicy
data.description: Represents the type of insurance policy, such as auto, home, life, or annuity.

data.label: Case
data.description: Represents a case, which is a customer issue or problem.

data.label: WorkOrder
data.description: Represents field service work to be performed for a customer. This object is available in API version 36.0 and later.

data.label: User
data.description: Represents a user in your organization.

data.label: AuthProvider
data.description: Represents an authentication provider (auth provider). An auth provider lets users log in to your Salesforce org from an external service provider, such as Facebook, Google, or GitHub.

data.label: ServiceContract
data.description: Represents a customer support contract (business agreement). This object is available in API version 18.0 and later.

data.label: Order
data.description: Represents an order associated with a contract or an account.

data.label: GroupClass
data.description: Represents the classification of group members that receive similar benefits. Example classes include executives, union, and office workers. Child object of employer or group Account. This object is available in API version 55.0 and later.

data.label: UserRole
data.description: Represents a user role in your organization.

data.label: ProducerSplitAssignment
data.description: Represents information about commission split associated with a producer that's used to process commission statement. This object is available in API version 61 and later.

data.label: Contract
data.description: Represents a contract (a business agreement) associated with an Account.

data.label: ProducerSplitRoleAssignment
data.description: Represents the revenue generating entities assocaited with an insurance policy and account. This object is available in API version 62 and later.

data.label: GroupCensus
data.description: Represents a snapshot of statistics about eligible members (employees or members) of a group (employer or association) and their legal dependents. Use this entity in quoting, rating, and the subsequent enrollment process. Child object of employer or group Account. This object is available in API version 55.0 and later.

data.label: Contact
data.description: Represents a contact, which is a person associated with an account.

data.label: QuoteLineItemRecipient
data.description: Represents a site, employee, or other entity for which services are being quoted. This could include details such as the recipient's name, contact information, associated site or location, and any specific requirements or preferences for the quoted services. This object is available in API version 62.0 and later.

data.label: Partner
data.description: Represents a partner relationship between two Account records or between an Opportunity record and an Account record.

data.label: MaintenancePlan
data.description: Represents a preventive maintenance schedule for one or more assets in field service.

data.label: GroupCensusMember
data.description: Represents personal information about a member, for example employee or association member, or their dependents. GroupCensusMember is used to estimate the insurance plan cost for the group. This object is also used in the enrollment process to retrieve the member and dependent details. Child object of GroupCensus. This object is available in API version 55.0 and later.

data.label: Producer
data.description: Represents an agent or an agency selling insurance.

data.label: PartnerNetworkConnection
data.description: Represents a Salesforce to Salesforce connection between Salesforce organizations.

data.label: Opportunity
data.description: Represents an opportunity, which is a sale or pending deal.

data.label: InsurancePolicyParticipant
data.description: A junction object that associates the InsurancePolicy object with the Account object. This object represents the participants of an insurance policy. Insurance policy participants include policy owners and beneficiaries.

data.label: Entitlement
data.description: Represents the customer support an account or contact is eligible to receive. This object is available in API version 18.0 and later. Entitlements may be based on an asset, product, or service contract.

data.label: Lead
data.description: Represents a prospect or lead.

data.label: BusinessLicense
data.description: Represents the licenses of a party role like healthcare provider or producer.

data.label: Asset
data.description: Represents an item of commercial value, such as a product sold by your company or a competitor, that a customer has purchased.

data.label: Quote
data.description:
Represents a quote, which is a record showing proposed prices for products and services. Available in API version 18.0 and later.
Quotes can be created from and synced with opportunities, and emailed as PDFs to customers

data.label: OperatingHours
data.description: Represents the hours in which a service territory, service resource, or account is available for work. OperatingHours is used by Field Service, Salesforce Scheduler, Salesforce Meetings, Sales Engagement, and Workforce Engagement. This object is available in API version 38.0 and later.

data.label: CommissionStatement
data.description: Represents commission summary associated with a party or Commission Statement Line Item. This object is available in API version 61 and later.

data.label: BrokerOfRecord
data.description: Represents a legal authority for the brokerage to act on behalf of their clients with insurance carriers. This object is available in API version 61 and later.
